body:
@calmh Thanks for the clarification.  However, after digging into this and looking at network traffic I have not identified anything else that would be interacting with api.github.com repeatedly and exhausting that rate limit that isn't traceable to syncthing.  I agree that there is a non-zero chance that syncthing is an innocent bystander but I haven't identified another culprit yet and I don't run any software that utilizes the GH API that I'm aware of.  I'll continue to look for something else though.

Also, it's not a cluster of 5 machines - it is a cluster of about 10-15 or so devices (not all of which are continuously connected) with only half of them behind this NAT gateway.  I'm not sure if that changes the situation at all.

Regardless, no matter what is going on I feel that checking the http status code and honoring the x-rate-limit flag should be a good improvement to consider.
